    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PNF WLS initialization memory management\n\n### Summary\nThe `phy_wls_init()` function in the PNF was not properly initializing the WLS memory management structures, causing unexpected behavior during PNF operation. This fix aligns the PNF initialization with the VNF implementation.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/wls_integration/wls_pnf.c`: Enhanced `phy_wls_init()` to properly initialize memory management structures\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/wls_integration/wls_common.c`: Moved common memory management functions from VNF to shared location\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/wls_integration/include/wls_common.h`: Added function declarations\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/wls_integration/wls_vnf.c`: Removed duplicate code now in common file\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the PNF with WLS transport, the `phy_wls_init()` function would return successfully but subsequent memory operations would fail due to uninitialized memory management structures. This manifested as segmentation faults during message processing or incorrect message handling.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure OAI 5G with WLS transport enabled\n2. Start PNF with WLS interface\n3. Observe segmentation fault or memory access errors during initial message exchange\n\nThe fix ensures proper initialization of mutexes, memory arrays, and block queues similar to the VNF implementation.\n"
}